  "prompt": "What is the CFA exam?",
  "response": "The CFA (Chartered Financial Analyst) exam is a professional certification for investment and financial professionals, offered by the CFA Institute. Here are key details:\n\n1. Overview\n- Globally recognized credential in investment management\n- Considered one of the most prestigious designations in finance\n- Demonstrates expertise in investment analysis, portfolio management, and financial ethics\n\n2. Exam Structure\n- Three levels of examination: Level I, II, and III\n- Each level is a different exam taken on separate dates\n- Covers topics like economics, financial reporting, equity investments, fixed income, derivatives, and alternative investments\n\n3. Exam Requirements\n- Candidates must pass all three levels\n- Each exam is extremely challenging, with historically low pass rates\n- Typically requires 300+ hours of study per level\n- Requires a bachelor's degree or equivalent professional experience\n\n4. Professional Benefits\n- Enhances career opportunities in investment management\n- Signals advanced financial knowledge and analytical skills\n- Recognized by employers worldwide\n- Often required or preferred for roles like financial analyst, portfolio manager, research analyst\n\n5. Eligibility\n- Open to candidates with a bachelor's degree or equivalent professional experience\n- Must have 4 years of professional work experience to earn the charter\n\nThe CFA exam is known for its rigor and is considered a significant achievement in the finance profession.",
